cs.HCI, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CYBER, cs.LG 

The paper focuses on the development of an interactive visual interface for ORES, a machine learning-based web service for Wikimedia projects such as Wikipedia. The interface aims to assist Wikipedia editors in finding damaging edits by visualizing the relationship between major model metrics and a parameter. This suggests that the paper could be categorized under Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HCI) as it deals with the development of a user interface. Additionally, the paper involves Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with the optimization of a machine learning model for text classification. It also involves Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with the analysis of text data. Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) is another possible category as the paper deals with the detection of damaging edits. Finally, the paper involves Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it deals with the development of a machine learning-based web service.
